      "message": "There\u0027s one issue with compressed fields. Imagine you want to load an entity, update its (non-proto) field and store it back. It will uselessly decompress/compress back proto fields burning CPU. Python doesn\u0027t have this problem, since it decompresses on a field access (not when loading). Not sure how to avoid that. If go had generics, we could have `field *Compressed[Message]`, alas...\n\nSo I feel \"compressed\" is a foot gun.\n\n(Haven\u0027t looked at the CL yet).",
